ets to highlight your top 4-8 skills. We recommend listing skills in short, 2-3 word phrases, without punctuation.</li><li>Review your skills to make sure they match the job description. Any matches should be listed first.</li><li>Don’t forget about soft skills. For example, leadership - whether you coached a youth soccer league or served as president to a club.</li>",sectionTypeCd:"HILT",name:"Skills",defaultText:"Add ready-to-use skills or write your own.",title:"",definition:"In this 2-column section, use bullets to highlight your top 4-8 skills. We recommend listing skills in short, 2-3 word phrases, without punctuation.",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!0},{tips:"<li>Include up to 10 years of recent work experience, beginning with your current or most recent employer.</li><li>Use bullets to list your major accomplishments and experience so employers can easily scan your resume.</li><li>If you have relevant work experience from more than 10 years ago, we recommend adding a separate section called Previous Work Experience.</li>",sectionTypeCd:"EXPR",name:"Experience",defaultText:"Type in your responsibilities, achievements and job details. Need help? Use the pre-written examples by clicking the Add button on the {0} side",definition:"Outline up to 10 years of recent work experience, beginning with your current employer. Use bullets to list your major efforts, accomplishments and experience. If you have relevant work experience from more than 10 years ago, we recommend adding a separate section called Previous Work History.",title:"",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!0},{tips:"Use this section to highlight skills and assets unique to the executive experience. More than a list of job duties, Executive Experience should focus on the achievements that brought you to the c-suite level.",sectionTypeCd:"EEXP",name:"Executive Experience",defaultText:"Enter details about what you did in your previous jobs. Start with your responsibilities, but also include results and achievements.",definition:"Use this section to highlight skills and assets unique to the executive experience. More than a list of job duties, Executive Experience should focus on the acheivements that brought you to the c-suite level.",title:"",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"Your military experience is a great asset. Most employers value veterans for their skills, integrity and service. Ideally you should integrate transferrable skills from your military experience throughout your resume, but you can also highlight additional achievements here.",sectionTypeCd:"MILI",name:"Military Experience",defaultText:"Describe your service in the military here, focusing on skills that will transfer to civilian jobs.",definition:"Your military experience is a great asset. Most employers value veterans for their skills, integrity and service. Ideally you should integrate transferrable skills from your military experience throughout your resume, but you can also highlight additional achievements here.",title:"",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"<li>Before you write your education section, read the job description to find what degrees or certifications are required.</li><li>If you have earned a college degree, you do not need to include your high school degree (or GED certification) on your resume.</li><li>Your most recent degree should be the first entry in your education section.</li>",sectionTypeCd:"EDUC",name:"Education and Training",defaultText:"",title:"",definition:"Any degrees, coursework, professional development or training programs you have completed in preparation for your target job.",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!0},{tips:"",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"AFIL",definition:"",name:"Activities and Honors",defaultText:"Type in your activities and honors. Need help? Use the pre-written examples by clicking the Add button on the {0} side",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"ACCM",definition:"",name:"Accomplishments",defaultText:"Type in your accomplishments. Need help? Use the pre-written examples by clicking the Add button on the {0} side",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"ADDI",definition:"",name:"Additional Information",defaultText:"Type in your additional information",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"CERT",definition:"",name:"Certifications",defaultText:"Type in your certifications. Need help? Use the pre-written examples by clicking the Add button on the {0} side",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"ALNK",definition:"",name:"Websites, Portfolios, Profiles",defaultText:"",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"CUST",definition:"",name:"",defaultText:"Type in your details",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"Add any technical skills, including but not limited to computer skills.",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"TSKL",definition:"Any technical skills, including but not limited to computer skills.",name:"Technical Skills",defaultText:"List specific technical skills employers may want to see, such as specific software, tools and programming languages.",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"This section is a summary paragraph consisting of 3-5 sentences focusing on the highlights of your career and abilities.",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"ESUM",definition:"A summary paragraph consisting of 3-5 sentences focusing on the highlights of your career and abilities.",name:"Executive Summary",defaultText:"Enter a brief description of your professional background. You can choose to highlight specific skills, knowledge or industry experience.",defaultTextESUM2:"Enter 4-6 areas of expertise you'd like to feature.",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1},{tips:"<li>A1 Beginner: Can understand simple phrases and ask basic questions.</li><li>A2 Elementary: Can have short conversations and provide routine information.</li><li>B1 Intermediate: Can have slightly more complex conversations and communicate in past and future tenses.</li><li>B2 Upper-intermediate: Can communicate confidently in most professional or academic settings.</li><li>C1 Advanced: Has a strong command of the language and can read and discuss complex material.</li><li>C2 Proficient: Can communicate with the skill and ease of a native speaker.</li>",title:"",sectionTypeCd:"LNGG",definition:"",name:"Languages",defaultText:"",doczonetypecd:"BODY",isDefaut:!1}];const b={summTailoring:{experimentId:"1724fca3-f26b-4508-bdfc-f4a84685d95f",userStageId:"Finalize",rdlKey:"summTailoringV2",IsBackend:!1,Country:["All"],experimentName:"RN Finalize Dummy Summary Tailoring Finalize All Desktop V1 CVR",conductforguestusers:!0,newExperimentJS:!0}},y=e=>{for(var t=e+"=",n=document.cookie.split(";"),o=0;o<n.length;o++){for(var a=n[o];" "==a.charAt(0);)a=a.substring(1,a.length);if(0==a.indexOf(t))return a.substring(t.length,a.length)}return null},C=e=>h(void 0,void 0,void 0,(function*(){let t=null;t=y("vstr");let n=0,o=b[e];if(b[e].isActive){let e=yield((e,t)=>{var n=L()+"visitors/"+e+"/experiments/"+t;return new Promise((function(e,t){x(n,"GET",!0,!0,(function(t){t&&(t=JSON.parse(t)),e(t)}),null,null,!0)})).then((function(e){return e})).catch((function(e){return null}))})(t,o.experimentId);e&&e.isSuccess&&e.data&&(n=e.data.variant)}return n})),S=e=>{var t=0,n=y("runtest");if(n){var o=n.split(",").filter((function(t){return-1!=t.indexOf(e+"_")}));if(o&&o.length>0)2==o[0].split("_").length&&(t=parseInt(o[0].split("_")[1]))}return t},T=(e,t)=>h(void 0,void 0,void 0,(function*(){try{const o=yield((e,t)=>function(n){return c.UserAjaxHelper.GetUserAllExperimentsV3(e,t).then(e=>e)})(e,t)(()=>{});let a=o&&o.experiments||[];for(var n in b)if(Object.prototype.hasOwnProperty.call(b,n)){let e=b[n],t=S(e.experimentId);if(t>0)return t;if(e.isActive||e.newExperimentJS){const n=a.find(t=>t.experiment_uid==e.experimentId);if(n)return t=n.variant,n.variant}else if(e.isActive&&e.isVisitorExperiment&&!t){return C(e.rdlKey)}}return 0}c